<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881004-0034 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell Douglas Wins Defense Jobs </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RTN HSC GM GME GMH MD LIT BA F GE ITT </CO><IN> ARO </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   McDonnell Douglas Corp. won $342.3 million in contracts for Air Force shuttle support and ground-based surveillance equipment, and for Navy F-18 electronics equipment.    Litton Corp.'s Ingalls Shipbuilding Division received a $341.4 million Navy contract for an amphibious warfare ship.    Boeing Co. got $94.3 million in contracts for Army helicopter research and Navy and Air Force aircraft modifications.    Ford Aerospace Corp., a unit of Ford Motor Co., was awarded a $70.2 million Air Force contract for satellite tracking.    General Electric Co. was issued $57.5 million in Air Force contracts for aircraft modifications, satellite equipment and radar-station support.    ITT Corp. won $57.1 million in Air Force contracts for various missile-warning systems.    The BMY Division of Harsco Corp. was given a $46.8 million Army contract for trucks.    Electronic Data Systems Corp., a unit of General Motors Corp., received a $45.6 million Army contract for data processing.    Aerojet General Corp. was issued $40.3 million in Air Force contracts for satellite support and rocket loaders.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors, got a $34.5 million Air Force contract for bombs.    Analytical Services Inc., a unit of Hannaford Bros. Co., received a $29.3 million Air Force contract for research and development.    Raytheon Service Co., a unit of Raytheon Co., won a $23.8 million Air Force contract for radar support. </TEXT></DOC>